# Synthetic MAC file for manual testing and validation of the TUI MAC viewer.
#
# Pair with A2L: examples/update_test1.a2l
#   (Tag names here match MEASUREMENT/CHARACTERISTIC symbols in that file.)
#
# Suggested workflow:
#   1. Start the TUI and load this file as the data file (.mac).
#   2. Load A2L -> choose examples/update_test1.a2l
#   3. Switch to MAC view (MAC view button).
#   4. Expect mostly green rows for the real symbols below (InA2L=yes, Status=OK).
#   5. Expect red for UNKNOWN_TAG_NOT_IN_A2L (NOT_IN_A2L), malformed lines (ERR_PARSE).
#
# Note: Addresses in this file are illustrative; update_test1.a2l uses 0x0 for many
# ECU_ADDRESS entries. InMem stays n/a when only a .mac is loaded (no S19/HEX image).

# --- Valid rows (names exist in update_test1.a2l) ---
Measurement_Value=0x0
Characteristic_Value=0x0
Curve_ExternalAxis=00000000
Curve_InternalAxis=00000000
Measurement_Matrix=0x20000100
Measurement_Bitfield_bits1=0x20000104
Measurement_Enum=0x20000108

# --- Deliberate validation cases ---
UNKNOWN_TAG_NOT_IN_A2L=70001a88

this line has no equals sign

BAD_HEX_ADDRESS=GGGG

# end
